ApiVersion.name: api-version
ApiVersion.description: Version number of Azure LBS API.  Current version is 1.0

AcceptLanguage.name: Accept-Language
AcceptLanguage.description: Specifies the list of acceptable ISO 639-1 language codes in which the timezone names should be returned.

TimezoneOptions.name: options
TimezoneOptions.description: Alternatively, use alias "o". Options available for types of information returned in the result.

values.description: Do not include zoneinfo or transitions in the result.
Include additional time zone info in the result.
Include transition information in the result (The number of transitions is currently capped at 250).
Include both zoneinfo and transitions in the result.

TimezoneTimeStamp.name: timeStamp
TimezoneTimeStamp.description: Alternatively, use alias "stamp", or "s". Reference time, if omitted, the API will use the machine time serving the request.

TimezoneTransitionsFrom.name: transitionsFrom
TimezoneTransitionsFrom.description: Alternatively, use alias "tf". The start date from which daylight savings time (DST) transitions are requested, only applies when "options" = all or "options" = transitions.

TimezoneTransitionsYears.name: transitionsYears
TimezoneTransitionsYears.description: Alternatively, use alias "ty". The number of years from "transitionsFrom" for which DST transitions are requested, only applies when "options" = all or "options" = transitions.

TextFormat.name: format
TextFormat.description: Desired format of the response. Possible values are json & xml.

RasterTileFormat.name: format
RasterTileFormat.description: Desired format of the response. Possible value: png.

values.description: An image in the png format. Supports zoom levels 0 through 18.

TileFormat.name: format
TileFormat.description: Desired format of the response. Possible values are png & pbf.

values.description: An image in the png format. Supports zoom levels 0 through 18.
Vector graphic in the pbf format. Supports zoom levels 0 through 20.

xTileIndex.name: x
xTileIndex.description: X index for the desired tile, based on Spherical Mercator projection coordinate system (EPSG:3857)

yTileIndex.name: y
yTileIndex.description: Y index for the desired tile, based on Spherical Mercator projection coordinate system (EPSG:3857)

Text.name: text
Text.description: Yes/no value to exclude textual data from response. Only images and country names will be in response.

Language.name: language
Language.description: Language in which search results should be returned. Should be one of supported IETF language tags, case insensitive. When data in specified language is not available for a specific field, default language is used

OptionalBiasLat.name: lat
OptionalBiasLat.description: Latitude where results should be biased.  E.g. 37.337

OptionalBiasLon.name: lon
OptionalBiasLon.description: Longitude where results should be biased.  E.g. -121.89

RequiredBiasLat.name: lat
RequiredBiasLat.description: Latitude where results should be biased.  E.g. 37.337

RequiredBiasLon.name: lon
RequiredBiasLon.description: Longitude where results should be biased.  E.g. -121.89

Typeahead.name: typeahead
Typeahead.description: Boolean.  If the typeahead flag is set, the query will be interpreted as a partial input and the search will enter predictive mode

Limit.name: limit
Limit.description: Maximum number of responses that will be returned.

CountrySet.name: countrySet
CountrySet.description: Comma separated string of country codes, e.g. FR, ES. This will limit the search to the specified countries

Radius.name: radius
Radius.description: The radius in meters to for the results to be constrained to the defined area

Query.name: query
Query.description: The applicable query string and/or coordinates

SearchResultIndexSet.name: idxSet
SearchResultIndexSet.description: A comma separated list of indexes which should be utilized for the search. Item order does not matter. Available indexes are: Addr = Address range interpolation, Geo = Geographies, PAD = Point Addresses, POI = Points of interest, Str = Streets, Xstr = Cross Streets (intersections)

BoundingBoxTopLeft.name: topLeft
BoundingBoxTopLeft.description: Top left position of the bounding box.  E.g. 37.553,-122.453

BoundingBoxBottomRight.name: btmRight
BoundingBoxBottomRight.description: Bottom right position of the bounding box. E.g. 37.553,-122.453

400.description: Bad request: one or more parameters were incorrectly specified or are mutually exclusive.

401.description: Unauthorized: Access is denied due to invalid credentials.

404.description: Not Found: the requested resource could not be found, but it may be available again in the future.

500.description: An error occurred while processing the request. Please try again later.

poi.description: A single traffic incident, or a cluster of traffic incidents

p.description: The point where an icon of the cluster or raw incident should be drawn, expressed in the requested projection. This is affected by traffic style, zoom level and road type

ic.description: The icon category associated with this incident. Values are numbers in the range 0-13, with the following meanings

ty.description: The magnitude of delay associated with incident. These values correspond to incident colors in the traffic tiles

cbl.description: Bottom left coordinate of the cluster in the projection of the request

ctr.description: Top right coordinate of the cluster in the projection of the request

cs.description: Cluster size: the number of incidents in the cluster

l.description: Length of the incident in meters

r.description: The road number(s) affected by the incident. Multiple road numbers will delimited by slashes

dl.description: Delay caused by the incident in seconds (except in road closures)

t.description: To: the name of the intersection or location where the traffic due to the incident ends

f.description: From: the name of the intersection or location where the traffic due to the incident starts

d.description: Description of the incident in the language requested

c.description: Cause of the incident, where available, in the language requested

LineStringGeoJson.description: A GeoJSON compliant LineString Geometry object

type.description: Type property. This value must be equal to LineString.

coordinates.description: Coordinates for the LineString object. Each Position object in Coordinates should be GeoJSON compliant i.e. longitude precedes latitute. Refer to RFC7946 for details.
